2C%20while%20de-emphasizing%20financial%20regulation%20and%20corporate%20crime%20prosecution%20%E2%80%94%20closing%20some%20of%20the%20usual%20off-ramps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20revolving%20door%20is%20jammed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecruiters%20and%20lawyers%20in%20and%20outside%20government%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20it's%20increasingly%20hard%20to%20move%20from%20public%20to%20private%20sector%20work%3A%20there's%20a%20large%20supply%20of%20job%20seekers%2C%20and%20comparatively%20low%20demand%20for%20their%20expertise%20and%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20federal%20lawyer%20who%20recently%20resigned%20said%20it%20took%20him%20months%20to%20find%20a%20new%20job%20despite%20working%20in%20a%20prestigious%20role%2C%20forcing%20him%20to%20stay%20at%20his%20job%20longer%20than%20he%20wanted.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20a%20responsibility%20to%20my%20family%20to%20bring%20home%20a%20paycheck%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d13272a8-71c2-432e-8b82-aed797eb9b3c%5C%22%3EWhite%20collar%20slowdown%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20the%20roughly%2040%2C000%20lawyers%20who%20work%20for%20the%20US%20government%20can%20parlay%20their%20experience%20drafting%2C%20interpreting%2C%20and%20enforcing%20a%20dense%20thicket%20of%20laws%20and%20regulations%20into%20well-paid%20jobs%20for%20law%20firms%20and%20large%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20few%20months%2C%20law%20firms%20across%20Washington%20and%20in%20New%20York%20have%20been%20inundated%20with%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%2C%20and%20they're%20being%20choosy%2C%20especially%20when%20hiring%20white-collar%20criminal%20defense%20lawyers%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20former%20federal%20prosecutors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhite-collar%20demand%20is%20down%20across%20the%20board%2C%26quot%3B%20whether%20it%20comes%20to%20recruiting%20from%20the%20government%20or%20poaching%20a%20partner%20with%20an%20established%20clientele%20from%20another%20law%20firm%2C%20said%20Karen%20Vladeck%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Risepoint%20Search%20Partners%2C%20a%20legal%20recruiting%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20your%20standard%20white-collar%20partner%20right%20now%2C%20they%20want%20to%20see%20twice%20as%20much%20business%20as%20they%20want%20to%20see%20from%20another%20practice.%26quot%3B%20In%20other%20words%2C%20law%20firms%20are%20skeptical%20that%20hotshot%20criminal%20defense%20lawyers%20can%20reel%20in%20the%20kind%20of%20revenue%20that%20they%20used%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20headhunter%20told%20BI%20that%20only%20%26quot%3Bvery%20senior%26quot%3B%20lawyers%20coming%20out%20of%20US%20Attorney's%20Offices%20were%20getting%20interviews%20%E2%80%94%20and%20even%20those%20candidates%20were%20taking%20haircuts%20on%20compensation.%20The%20same%20job%20seeker%20who%20might%20have%20been%20able%20to%20get%20an%20offer%20for%20%241%20million%20or%20%241.2%20million%20in%20the%20past%20as%20a%20defense-and-investigations%20specialist%20might%20get%20%24750%2C000%20today%2C%20the%20headhunter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20issue%2C%20said%20Jack%20Zaremski%2C%20who%20runs%20Hanover%20Search%20Partners%2C%20is%20that%20Big%20Law%20firms%20already%20have%20a%20deep%20bench%20of%20white-collar%20litigators%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20partner%20at%20a%20large%20law%20firm%20said%20there%20isn't%20much%20work%20to%20go%20around%20for%20colleagues%20who%20focus%20on%20that%20kind%20of%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhite-collar%20criminal%20enforcement%20has%20been%20declining%20since%20the%20Obama%20administration%2C%20according%20to%20Syracuse%20University's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftracreports.org%2Freports%2F760%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETransactional%20Records%20Access%20Clearinghouse%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20compiles%20federal%20law-enforcement%20data.%20The%20number%20of%20white-collar%20criminal%20cases%20filed%20yearly%20fell%20from%20a%20high%20of%20more%20than%2010%2C000%20in%20the%20mid-1990s%20to%20about%204%2C300%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20prosecutions%20were%20down%2C%20there%20was%20still%20work%20for%20Big%20Law's%20ex-prosecutors%20keeping%20their%20clients%20out%20of%20court.%20After%20the%202009%20financial%20crash%2C%20banks%20needed%20outside%20help%20dealing%20with%20crisis-related%20investigations%2C%20the%20large%20law%20firm%20partner%20said.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftraders-at-four-banks-are-being-investigated-in-the-libor-probe-and-wall-street-may-start-eating-its-own-2012-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2012%20Libor%20scandal%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20similar%20rate-rigging%20allegations%20led%20to%20even%20more%20work.%20That%20has%20pretty%20much%20dried%20up%2C%20the%20partner%20said%2C%20and%20banks'%20in-house%20lawyers%20can%20do%20some%20of%20the%20work%20that%20they%20used%20to%20have%20to%20outsource.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%2C%20who%20was%20convicted%20of%20falsifying%20business%20records%2C%20has%20shown%20skepticism%20for%20white-collar%20criminal%20enforcement.%20His%20Justice%20Department%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Finvestigations%2Fhow-trump-defanged-justice-departments-political-corruption-watchdogs-2025-06-09%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslashed%20its%20corruption%20unit%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fdoj-backs-off-plan-spread-its-tax-division-across-us-2025-04-21%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emade%20moves%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20close%20its%20tax%20division%20and%20fold%20its%20responsibilities%20into%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20agency.%20One%20of%20his%20early%20executive%20orders%20paused%20cases%20under%20the%20Foreign%20Corrupt%20Practices%20Act%2C%20which%20bans%20paying%20bribes%20to%20foreign%20officials%20to%20get%20business.%20(Several%20have%20since%20resumed.)%20He%20has%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdemocrats-judiciary.house.gov%2Fsites%2Fevo-subsites%2Fdemocrats-judiciary.house.gov%2Ffiles%2Fevo-media-document%2F2025-06-17.dem-memo-re-%25241.3b-cost-of-trump-pardons.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epardoned%3C%2Fa%3E%20people%20and%20companies%20that%20collectively%20owed%20%241.3%20billion%20for%20offenses%20like%20securities%20fraud%20and%20tax%20evasion%2C%20erasing%20their%20debts%20to%20the%20government%20and%20their%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMatthew%20Burke%2C%20a%20former%20federal%20prosecutor%20on%20the%20team%20led%20by%20Jack%20Smith%20that%20charged%20Donald%20Trump%20with%20keeping%20classified%20documents%20after%20his%20presidency%20and%20trying%20to%20subvert%20the%202020%20election%2C%20said%20that%20while%20his%20experience%20deterred%20some%20potential%20employers%2C%20it%20attracted%20others.%20Scale%20LLP%2C%20a%20firm%20of%20about%2080%20lawyers%20that%20focuses%20on%20the%20tech%20sector%2C%20said%20in%20May%20that%20Burke%20would%20lead%20its%20investigations%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20undoubtedly%20were%20doors%20that%20were%20closed%20to%20me%20because%20of%20what%20I've%20done%2C%20but%20there%20will%20also%20be%20doors%20that%20will%20be%20opened%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20It's%20been%20%26quot%3Binformative%20to%20know%20what%20doors%20have%20been%20closed%20and%20which%20have%20been%20opened%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20criminal%20cases%20where%20the%20administration's%20approach%20is%20being%20felt.%20Some%20financial%20regulatory%20lawyers%20are%20also%20stuck%20in%20a%20tightening%20job%20market%2C%20as%20the%20administration%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feliminate-cfpb-trump-elon-musk-overdraft-fees-medical-bills-bessent-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattempts%20to%20pare%20down%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20former%20bureau%20lawyer%20said%20that%20among%20some%20people%20who%20have%20managed%20to%20stay%20employed%2C%20the%20common%20attitude%20is%20%26quot%3BThey're%20gonna%20have%20to%20drag%20me%20out%20of%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration's%20efforts%20to%20reduce%20headcount%20at%20the%20Bureau%20have%20been%20put%20on%20hold%20by%20the%20courts.%20The%20CFPB%20employees'%20union%20said%20in%20an%20email%20that%20some%20of%20its%20members%20have%20taken%20other%20jobs%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bmany%20more%20remain%20ready%20to%20get%20back%20to%20the%20work%20we%20were%20hired%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2222ba0447-308c-4e42-a562-faf485d21ecb%5C%22%3EJob%20market%20challenges%20aren't%20universal%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20CFPB%20managers%20have%20been%20able%20to%20parlay%20their%20experience%20into%20jobs%20at%20financial%20technology%20firms%2C%20law%20firms%2C%20and%20banks%20or%20credit%20unions%2C%20the%20former%20bureau%20lawyer%20said.%20And%20some%20people%20leaving%20the%20Justice%20Department%20are%20still%20in%20high%20demand.%20Deep%20familiarity%20with%20international%20trade%20restrictions%20and%20export-control%20laws%20makes%20some%20lawyers%20valuable%20to%20tech%20companies%20worried%20about%20running%20afoul%20of%20US%20sanctions%20and%20trade%20restrictions.%20Antitrust%20experience%20is%20also%20a%20plus%2C%20Vladeck%20and%20others%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECharles%20Cain%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission's%20FCPA%20Unit%2C%20went%20to%20work%20at%20EY%2C%20according%20to%20a%20LinkedIn%20post.%20He%20was%20one%20of%20at%20least%20five%20lawyers%20who%20announced%20their%20departures%20from%20the%20unit%20at%20a%20meeting%20in%20late%20March%2C%20according%20to%20Mark%20Yost%2C%20a%20former%20member%20of%20the%20unit%20who%20was%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20former%20feds%20are%20having%20a%20much%20tougher%20time%20on%20the%20job%20market.%20Waves%20of%20civil%20rights%20lawyers%20have%20been%20fired%20or%20left%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnational-security%2F2025%2F04%2F28%2Fjustice-civil-rights-harmeet-dhillon-trump%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJustice%20Department%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20agencies%2C%20like%20the%20Department%20of%20Education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20only%20so%20many%20civil%20rights-related%20jobs%20out%20there%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20competing%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stacey%20Young%2C%20a%20former%20Justice%20Department%20attorney%20who%20leads%20the%20networking%20group%20Justice%20Connection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20competition%20for%20open%20roles%2C%20relatively%20few%20lawyers%2C%20regardless%20of%20where%20they%20work%2C%20are%20quitting%20or%20being%20terminated%20without%20something%20lined%20up.%20While%20the%20D.C.%20area%20unemployment%20rate%20has%20ticked%20upward%2C%20the%20national%20rate%20for%20legal%20occupations%20%E2%80%94%20a%20group%20of%20about%201.8%20million%20people%20of%20whom%201.1%20million%20are%20lawyers%20%E2%80%94%20was%202.1%25%20in%20May%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%2C%20below%20the%204%25%20average%20across%20the%20US%20workforce.%20For%20lawyers%2C%20a%20smaller%20group%20of%20workers%20for%20which%20estimates%20are%20less%20reliable%2C%20the%20first-quarter%20unemployment%20rate%20was%20about%201%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20a%20glut%20of%20supply%20on%20the%20job%20market%20means%20lawyers%20will%20need%20to%20broaden%20their%20search.%20Vladeck%20tells%20job%20seekers%20to%20think%20of%20landing%20their%20next%20job%20outside%20government%20as%20a%20Trivial%20Pursuit%20pie%2C%20with%20each%20slice%20representing%20a%20more%20niche%20avenue%20for%20employment%3A%20boutique%20firms%2C%20in-house%20counsel%20roles%2C%20nonprofits%2C%20or%20legal-adjacent%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20order%20to%20get%20a%20job%20in%20this%20market%2C%20you%20have%20to%20pay%20attention%20to%20each%20of%20those%20slices%2C%26quot%3B%20Vladeck%20said.%20%26quot%3B