out%20everything%20from%20our%20employees%20to%20cybersecurity%20training.%20It's%20very%20manual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20one%20team%20decide%20they'd%20try%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20make%20investor%20diligence%20easier.%20Despite%20having%20just%20one%20technologist%2C%20this%20team%20found%20a%20solution%20to%20automate%20the%20process%2C%20which%20we're%20launching%20later%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20seek%20to%20empower%20people%20to%20solve%20things%20themselves%2C%20with%20embedded%20technologists%20across%20the%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20experienced%20more%20challenges%20dealing%20with%20regulatory%20restrictions%20on%20large%20language%20models%20globally.%20We%20learned%20the%20hard%20way%20that%20these%20regulatory%20hurdles%20require%20a%20lot%20of%20evaluation.%20We're%20launching%20solutions%2C%20but%20it's%20taking%20longer%20than%20expected%20to%20deploy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20think%20you%20can%20go%20fast%20with%20AI%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20always%20work%20that%20way%2C%20especially%20in%20today's%20global%20climate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHas%20any%20single%20piece%20of%20career%20advice%20stuck%20with%20you%20over%20the%20years%2C%20and%20what%20is%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20on%2C%20I%20was%20advised%20to%20always%20raise%20my%20hand%20for%20the%20extra%20hard%20assignments.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20take%20a%20risk%20and%20bet%20on%20yourself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20are%20immigrants%2C%20and%20I%20learned%20work%20ethic%2C%20courage%2C%20and%20audacity%20from%20them.%20But%20when%20I%20entered%20the%20workforce%2C%20I%20had%20impostor%20syndrome.%20With%20blue-collar%20parents%2C%20the%20office%20environment%20was%20completely%20different%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20taking%20on%20difficult%20assignments%2C%20I%20created%20relationships%20and%20visibility%20and%20was%20able%20to%20learn%20and%20grow%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETell%20me%20about%20your%20parents.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20from%20the%20Azores%20Islands%20in%20Portugal.%20They%20came%20to%20the%20US%20during%20the%20dictatorship%20years.%20My%20dad%20only%20went%20to%20school%20up%20until%20the%20age%20of%2010%2C%20because%20his%20family%20could%20not%20afford%20to%20pay%20for%20more%20education.%20He%20can%20add%2C%20subtract%2C%20and%20multiply%2C%20but%20was%20never%20taught%20how%20to%20divide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20came%20to%20the%20US%20after%20serving%20in%20the%20Portuguese%20Army%20to%20give%20his%20family%20a%20better%20future.%20He%20knew%20no%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20became%20a%20custodian%2C%20cleaning%20schools%2C%20and%20had%20a%20side%20hustle%20selling%20house%20plants%20at%20a%20flea%20market%20on%20the%20weekends.%20We%20all%20helped%20cultivate%20and%20sell%20the%20plants.%20I%20learned%20a%20lot%20from%20my%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20does%20your%20morning%20routine%20look%20like%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20bicoastal%3A%20I%20spend%20one%20week%20a%20month%20in%20DC%20and%20also%20time%20in%20New%20York%2C%20but%20I%20live%20on%20the%20West%20Coast%20and%20work%20out%20of%20our%20Menlo%20Park%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20East%20coast%2C%20I%20might%20start%20my%20day%20%E2%80%94%20work%20permitting%20%E2%80%94%20listening%20to%20news%20podcasts%2C%20going%20for%20a%20run%2C%20meditating%2C%20and%20eating%20a%20healthy%20breakfast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20I%20start%20really%20early%20in%20the%20morning.%20I%20don't%20always%20get%20that%20workout%20in%2C%20but%20I%20start%20with%20some%20early%20calls%2C%20and%20then%20take%20a%20break%20to%20drive%20my%20daughter%20to%20school%20before%20heading%20to%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20get%20to%20my%20desk%2C%20I%20write%20down%20the%20day's%20priorities.%20I've%20done%20this%20my%20whole%20career%2C%20and%20try%20not%20to%20let%20constant%20fire%20drills%20overtake%20those%20priorities.%20When%20you're%20driving%20transform